secondary_outcome.description:
A health-related quality-of-life instrument that consists of a well-validated generic core measure and some condition and disease-specific modules. The instructions ask how much of a problem each item has been during the past 1 month. A 5-point response scale is utilized across child self-report and parent proxy report as follows:
0=never a problem;
almost never a problem;
sometimes a problem;
often a problem;
almost always a problem.

Patient Global Impression of Improvement (PGI-I).
A single item questionnaire to assess the patient's impression of improvement in dyskinesia symptoms after initiating therapy.
much improved (since the initiation of treatment);
somewhat improved;
no change;
somewhat worse;
much worse (since the initiation of treatment).
